            <div>
                <opener>
                    My darling Mother,
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    Just a little scrap
                    <lb/>
                    in Ninia’s letter I tell you -
                    <unclear quantity="3" unit="word"/>
                    -
                    <lb/>
                    staying in the house with Henschel so your
                    <lb/>
                    old Wildbad friend Herr von Roumanim!
                    <lb/>
                    He asked me if I had any relatives who
                    <lb/>
                    had been in Germany in ‘73 and
                    <lb/>
                    was so delighted to find out that you were
                    <lb/>
                    my mother of
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    . He
                    <hi rend="underlined">raves</hi>
                    about
                    <lb/>
                    Mary!! He is a pleasant man &
                    <lb/>
                    bade me remembers him most
                    <lb/>
                    kindly & respectfully & my Frau
                    <lb/>
                    Mutter &
                    <hi rend="underlined">Fräulein</hi>
                    Schwester! -
                    <lb/>
                    Also I was to tell you that now he wears
                    <lb/>
                    his hair
                    <hi rend="underlined">long</hi>
                    – not all cut short. As
                    <lb/>
                    when you knew him!!!!!
                    <lb/>
                    I have had several talks with
                    <lb/>
                    Hentschel about my music & am
                    <lb/>
                    most awfully happy about it.
                    <lb/>
                    He thinks more of my talent than
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="underlined">Even I did</hi>
                    !! - & has written ab’
                    <pb/>
                    me to
                    <hi rend="underlined">Brahms</hi>
                    – (with whom he was
                    <lb/>
                    almost brought up) & Simrock. All
                    <lb/>
                    live in Berlin and he says I
                    <lb/>
                    shall be received with
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    .
                    <lb/>
                    It is so glorious to be told by
                    <lb/>
                    competent persons that ones future lies in ones own hands –
                    <lb/>
                    that the material for realizing
                    <lb/>
                    hopes I hardly ever – I think
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="underlined">never</hi>
                    breathed at home even – is there – &
                    <lb/>
                    I have but to work
                    <lb/>
                    hard & steadily &
                    <hi rend="underlined">not</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">be</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">too</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="underlined">soon</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">pleased</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">with</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">myself</hi>
                    .
                    <lb/>
                    Everyday I become more & more
                    <lb/>
                    convinced of the truth of my
                    <lb/>
                    old axiom –
                    <lb/>
                    that why no women
                    <lb/>
                    have become composers is because
                    <pb/>
                    <hi rend="underlined">they have married</hi>
                    - & then very pro-
                    <lb/>
                    perly made their husband & children
                    <lb/>
                    the first consideration – So even if I were to fall desperately
                    <hi rend="underlined">in love</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    with
                    <hi rend="underlined">Brahms</hi>
                    & he were to propose to
                    <lb/>
                    me –
                    <hi rend="underlined">I'd</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">say</hi>
                    <hi rend="underlined">no</hi>
                    !!!!! So fear not
                    <lb/>
                    that I shall marry in Germany!! -
                    <lb/>
                    I told Henschel my opinion and he
                    <lb/>
                    said that perhaps I was right but as he
                    <lb/>
                    himself has & I am told – an un-
                    <lb/>
                    glückliche Liebe on hand – I dont
                    <lb/>
                    think he’s a judge! He
                    <hi rend="underlined">is</hi>
                    so good to
                    <lb/>
                    me – corrects my songs for me (I
                    <lb/>
                    have composed lots more) – sets
                    <lb/>
                    me basses on which to construct
                    <lb/>
                    chorales & all sorts of things - & yet
                    <lb/>
                    I know if I were Henschel it would be
                    <lb/>
                    a great pleasure to me to get
                    <lb/>
                    hold of a new pupil to give a friendly shove on to – during a
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    do – nothing – stay in a little primitive town!!
                    <lb/>
                    Love Mother darling to the present goodbye –
                    <lb/>
                    I think of me always as very very happy - &
                    <hi rend="underlined">o so</hi>
                    well!!!!
                </p>
                <closer>
                    Dear love to all at home from your most loving child, Ethel.
                </closer>
